  , issueCommentBody =
      "Hi @timjrobinson, this is indeed by design.\r\nTo clarify on @nviennot 's branch in the update hint: You can write something like this\r\n```\r\nr.table('queuers')\r\n          .getAll(Queuer.STATES.searching, {index: 'state'})\r\n          .filter(db.row('userIds').count().eq(2))\r\n          .limit(2)\r\n          .update(\r\n              r.branch(\r\n                  r.row(\"state\").eq(\"Queuer.STATES.searching\"),\r\n                  {state: Queuer.STATES.waiting, matchId: matchId},\r\n                  {}),\r\n              {returnChanges: true})\r\n          .run conn, (err, result) =>\r\n            done(err, result)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe expression inside the update will be evaluated atomically. If the branch condition (the first argument to `branch`) evaluates to true, the update will be performed as before. If it evaluates to false, the update will not change the document."
  , issueCommentId = 60283038
